@startuml
title Optimisation Runtime Execution — Request to Result

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam noteBorderColor #A5B4FC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #EEF2FF

actor "User & OEX" as Caller
participant "OGW" as OGW
participant "OSB MS" as OSB
participant "NGW" as NGW
participant "OC MS" as OCMS
participant "OD MS" as ODMS
database "OC MS DB\nPostgreSQL" as OCDB
queue "OC MS Outbox" as Outbox
queue "Kafka\nt7.optimisation.events" as Kafka
participant "OW MS" as Worker
queue "OC MS Inbox" as Inbox
participant "OC Notification\nDelivery" as Notify
actor "Subscribed\nConsumer" as Subscriber

== Submit Runtime Optimisation ==

Caller -> OGW : 1. Start optimisation journey
OGW -> OGW : 2. Authenticate/session check\nand derive user context
OGW -> OSB : 3. Invoke OSB MS\nmTLS + User Context JWT\ncorrelationId and traceId

OSB -> OSB : 4. Apply user-context filtering\nand shape runtime request

OSB -> NGW : 5. Submit optimisation request\nmTLS + OAuth2 system identity\n(no user context downstream)

note right of NGW
User context stops before/at NGW.
Downstream OD and OC calls use service identity only.
end note

NGW -> OCMS : 6. POST /optimisation\nmTLS + service identity

== Validate Contract ==

OCMS -> ODMS : 7. Approved internal service-to-service path\nvalidate referenced ACTIVE\nOptimisationSpecification.id\nand expression.iri match
note right of ODMS
OC MS resolves and validates the referenced OD MS contract
through the approved internal service-to-service path.
end note

ODMS --> OCMS : ACTIVE specification\nexpressionSpecification.iri + targetEntitySchema

OCMS -> OCMS : 8. Validate expression.iri\nagainst expressionSpecification.iri\nand expression.expressionValue\nagainst targetEntitySchema\ncontext.targets[], constraints[], and preferences[]

== Persist Runtime Resource ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 9. Persist runtime Optimisation\ncreationContext.reason = NEW\nlifecycleStatus = ACKNOWLEDGED\nstore resolved OptimisationSpecification\nid, version, draftId, and href\nand accepted expression.iri
OCDB --> OCMS : Persisted

OCMS -> Outbox : 10. Write OptimisationRequestedEvent\ninstruction = EXECUTE\nsame transaction
Outbox --> OCMS : Outbox record stored

OCMS --> NGW : 11. 201 Created\nLocation + ETag + ACKNOWLEDGED resource
NGW --> OSB : 201 Created
OSB --> OGW : CreationResultView\nexecution remains asynchronous
OGW --> Caller : Optimisation created\nnot completed yet

== Publish OW MS Instruction ==

Outbox -> Kafka : 12. Publish OptimisationRequestedEvent\neventId + optimisationId\ncorrelationId + traceId
OCMS -> OCDB : 13. Advance ACKNOWLEDGED -> QUEUED\nafter successful Kafka publish

== Execute Optimisation Work ==

Kafka -> Worker : 14. OW MS consumes OptimisationRequestedEvent\ninstruction = EXECUTE
Worker -> Worker : 15. Resolve internal deterministic\nmodel binding
Worker -> Worker : 16. Invoke Gurobi Optimiser

Worker -> Kafka : 17. Publish OptimisationCompletedEvent\nstatus = COMPLETED, INFEASIBLE, or FAILED\nfor EXECUTE outcomes

== Project Outcome ==

Kafka -> Inbox : 18. Consume OptimisationCompletedEvent
Inbox -> Inbox : 19. Apply idempotency\nand stale/late event checks
Inbox -> OCDB : 20. Update lifecycle/result projection\nCOMPLETED, INFEASIBLE, FAILED,\nCANCELLED, or CANCELLATIONFAILED
OCDB --> Inbox : Projection stored

alt Matching /optimisation/hub subscription exists
  Inbox -> Notify : 21. Durable handoff for\nOptimisationStatusChangeEvent
  Notify -> Subscriber : 22. POST webhook notification\nsummary-only payload
  note right of Subscriber
  Webhook is notification only.
  Subscriber calls GET /optimisation/{id}
  for authoritative state/result.
  end note
end

== Poll or Fetch Authoritative Runtime Status ==

Caller -> OGW : 23. Poll or fetch optimisation status and result
OGW -> OSB : 24. Invoke OSB MS\nmTLS + User Context JWT
OSB -> OSB : 25. Authorise visibility\nusing user context
OSB -> NGW : 26. GET /optimisation/{id}\nmTLS + OAuth2 system identity\n(no user context downstream)
NGW -> OCMS : 27. Route GET /optimisation/{id}
OCMS -> OCDB : 28. Read lifecycle/result
OCDB --> OCMS : Current status and result
OCMS --> NGW : Return runtime Optimisation
NGW --> OSB : Return response
OSB --> OGW : Shape OptimisationDetailView
OGW --> Caller : Current optimisation status and result

@enduml
